Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 69
Edition:
Quote: lip like a motherless foal youngster accused of sulking or pouting; eg `There's no point in putting on that face.' My, my, Missy, you've got a lip there like a motherless foal.'  [Jean Henderson]
